my biggest tip for being a wedding photographer…

be the third wheel 🤙🏻

Sometimes it’s best to direct, lead, instruct and be loud but sometimes the beauty is in the moments you step back, shut up and remain unnoticeable. We’re capturing all the moments because when they get their photos back they may see a moment captured that takes them right back to the exact moment it happened during they day and if we can do that (as photographers) at least one time. We’re winners! 

Be that third wheel, wear that title with pride and go capture some moments not just photos 👏🏻👏🏻👏🏻

Am I the only who feels more burnt out the larger their to do list gets!? It’s a toxic cycle I know but the more there is on my plate the more I want to just shut down and take a nap 🤣

FOR THE LAST AND FINAL TIME IN 2022……..

ITS WEDDING DAY 🤍

I cannot believe that after today I’ve officially made it through 56 weddings of my own this year plus 10 that we’re shot by my team 🤍

I’m so grateful everyday that this is my job and 2022 has been challenging but also so damn rewarding to be apart of so many moments!! 

These two are my last and final couple of 2022 and it’s going to be such a gorgeous day and I cannot wait to celebrate but I’m also sooooooo sad for my 2022 season to officially be over!!

- 367 Hours spent Shooting
- 276,335 Images Photographed
- 44,809 Images Delivered 
- 1 broken ankle
- 16 Cities
- 4752749 Drunk guests
- 3 hours spent waiting because @stacielynnphotography always late.
- 56 pep talks about not overbooking myself
- Countless Dance Parties
- 657 hours spent running around doing sh*t that’s not in my job description
- Multiple breakdowns
- Endless times drinking alone in my office

& 56 of the most amazing clients who I’m so fucking grateful for having me apart of their day! 🤍

2022 was a hell of a ride and it had some serious highs and super low lows but every single moment of it was worth what I gained… the gratitude and the JOY! Congratulations to all the amazing couples of mine this year! 

As exhausting & draining this job is, both mentally and physically there is so much joy, love and passion I have for it and my clients that I may never stop! 🙌🏻

Thank you to each and every person I encountered this year, not just my clients but the guests, the families, the friends, the people that recognize me at a grocery store from their friends weddings, the vendors etc! Thank you for all the love, engagement, social media likes/shares/comments and all the other interactions along the way!!

This has been the best year yet and I cannot WAIT to see where it goes from here! 💪🏻

Midnights - Jordan’s Version ✨

I’ve traded in my Saturday plans to be apart of peoples big days which isn’t new information… but for the last few years I’ve traded in my NYE to celebrate at weddings and I’ve found SOOOOOO much joy in it! 

Knowing me I’d watch the early countdown and be asleep by 10 but now I get to not only shoot a wedding all day I get to join the party, dress up, toast, eat fancy food, and countdown to midnight amongst hundreds of wedding guests and it is exactly like every NYE party I want to go to but to lazy to actually go to! 

So tonight I’ll be repeating history and celebrating the end of 2022 while shooting a wedding and I’ll walk into 2023…. Also shooting a wedding with my friend @stacielynnphotography 🤣👌🏻

To anyone else enjoying themselves tonight, please be safe & make smart decisions because 2023 wants you apart of it! 🙌🏻✨

can we talk about how fasting is called (fast)ing and there ain’t nothing fuckkkkking fast about waiting 16 hours to eat again 🤣 like it’s 9:30 which means I haven’t been able to eat for over an hour and i can feel myself withering away into a thin dust being taken away with a slight breeze.

for the 1816272959 time, I’ll say it again…

You’re never going to regret taking 10 minutes out of your reception for sunset photos, I promise you! But more importantly… the absolute must do that I’m here to talk about is practicing your first dance one last time while the sun glows!

Bring a speaker, step away from the craziness and bring your photographer out for one last practice dance before the big reveal! It’s such an intimate moment with just you two in the evening glow and it will be just as special as the big first dance with everyone watching! 

Doing this will also give you 10 minutes of time for just you and your partner to relax, take a deep breathe, reconnect and share a moment of quiet, calmness and love! 

As a photographer this is one of my favourite moments of the day where I can step back, put my big boy voice away, let the moment play out and just capture such a genuine flawless moment! 🤍

they say good things take time….

this is why I always post so late a night 😏

… Even though most of you will see this in the morning because you’re not a night owl like myself. I wish I could tell you I’m having a raging Friday night but I just wrapped up my 4th game of solitaire and realized it’s after midnight 💪🏻👌🏻

I’d also like to brag that I’ve moved up to the “expert” level in solitaire so that’s a pretty huge Friday evening accomplishment if you ask me ✌🏻

after all my years of photographing people madly in love, the ones who start off by saying “we’re camera shy” are always the ones who bring out a little extra spice 🔥

No but on a serious note, I freakingggg love being able to bring two people who are a bit nervous in front of my camera and help them feel comfortable enough to show who they are 👌🏻 

The first step is to STRIP… no that doesn’t mean you need to strip down literally BUT you do need to strip down the doubt, the self sabotage, the walls, the guards and the expectations so you can be as present AF as you can with your significant other! Once all those barriers are gone and your “naked” then in that moment comes creating genuine, meaningful, authentic images together!

Love always, your favourite third wheel with a camera ✌🏻

Okay here’s the story…

So when I was first getting into wedding photography I booked my very first table at a wedding fair! I was so nervous I wasn’t going to stand out amount all the other photographers, I was worried I was going to get lost in the crowd with no way to separate myself from the rest! 

I thought to myself, what is something that could be included in a package that no one else has… IPADS! I personally love iPads so much and I use one almost daily for personal and business use! So I thought why not incorporate iPads into a wedding package where instead of the client getting a traditional wedding album, they get an iPad, personally engraved with their name and wedding date, pre loaded with all their wedding photos and ready to be used forever! 

As much as I absolutely LOVE wedding albums and I think everyone should have one, I also think that it’s 2023 and EVERYONE can find use for an iPad, heck we’re on technology 356 days a year anyways…

This idea was just something I had planned on doing as a way to be remembered from the wedding show YEARS ago but here we are still handing out iPads like I’m Oprah Winfrey all year long!! It was never something I intended to continue but as long as my clients still absolutley love the idea, I’ll still be purchasing them in bulk and needing security to walk me from the Apple Store to my car 🤣✌🏻

tomorrow is where we all win, single or not!

let’s be real, there’s always the “price shoppers” out there who just want to know your minimum dollar! 

These are most certainly AVOIDABLE clients. If they start off asking for a deal then I promise you they WILL NOT VALUE your work! Clients asking for a deal have already convinced themselves that your work isn’t worth what you’re selling it for, this is not the way to start a working relationship!

Sometimes in a retail setting you may see a discounted item, maybe it’s been used or maybe it isn’t totally perfect or maybe there isn’t as much of the product. So it’s discounted….

Your work for the client isn’t EVER going to be, half as good, or not sufficient or “less than” your other work so why the heck would you do and devalue yourself right from the get go! 

There will always be clients who value every penny they invest with you and they trust that the money their spending is in the hands of someone who believes in their own worth! 

Hold out for those clients because time and time again they will prove to you that these are the clients worth your time, energy, expertise and passion! 🤍

one thing you’ll always get from me is 10000% realism! Im not going to be this fake ass person who try’s to come off like I got my shit together because 90% of the time I don’t even know where my shit is 🤷🏼‍♂️

Im also not the photographer that’s going to give you some fake version of myself and then leave it at that, I’m going to show you me which comes with bad dad jokes, swear words and a lot of snorting while laughing. I want to leave that session having gained new friends not wondering what they thought of me.

The beauty of being this transparent about myself online is that I show you I may not be everyones cup of tea so the only people that book me are those who are ready so say f*ck the professionalism and drink from that cup of tea!

Our living room has been a source of chaos ever since we purchased a couch a couple years ago that ended up being total trash, broken down and we fought for a return but got no where! 

Ever since then the living room has been a dropping zone for everything and never really looked nice! It also was home to my beautiful custom desk but for the last year I’ve been leasing my office space so there was no need for it anymore! 

Also with the newest addition joining our family it was time for an update on the living room HARDCORE! We purchased an entire wall of floor to ceiling cabinetry for household storage but more importantly, hiding the damn toys! 

We also purchased this amazing new couch that can fit the whole family and big enough for me to sleep on when my pregnant wife and her maternity pillow take up the entire bed 🤣

AT HOME ENGAGEMENT SESSIONS ✨ 

This is 10000% encouraged, why bother leaving the comfort of your own home for your session? I absolutely LOVE being invited inside not only a little piece of my clients relationships but also inside their home to really capture them in their element! 

I always come prepared with things to do, wine to drink, cookies to bake, flour to throw around at each other, music to dance around to in the kitchen and a camera to capture all those amazing moments! 

Seriously, if your considering it or didn’t know it was an option… trust me when I say DO IT! 🙌🏻

Anyhoo, here’s to rooting for yourself, cheering from your own sideline and always putting yourself first 🙌🏻

A little something I always share with my incredible families before a family session...

👋🏼Please don't be offended if, at the beginning of our shoot, my initial hello and attention are directed towards your child(ren) rather than you, the parents. 

Why do I do this?

For me, creating a genuine connection in such a short span of time is essential when photographing a family. By prioritizing the first interaction with your child, I aim to establish a comfortable and trusting bond right from the start.

When a child feels at ease, they can naturally express themselves, be vulnerable, and fully engage throughout the session. And that's when the magic happens—those genuine, heartwarming moments that I'm here to capture! 

Let's face it, the real stars of the show at a family session are the kids! As much as we may try to steer the ship, they hold the reins.

These little ones not only deserve a safe and comfortable environment but also a space where they feel heard, understood, and where their needs are met. By providing these essential moments during our session, I can easily form a bond with them.

Personally, I absolutely LOVE taking a break from the fast-paced world of weddings to spend an evening with your beautiful family. Together, we'll play games, make fart noises, sing along to Coco Melon, and create memories that you'll cherish forever! 🤍

Our beautiful healthy baby boy came into the world mighty quick on Sunday evening at only 37 weeks! 

It was a scary day for so many reasons including the speed at which he joined us, total time was only 4 hours from labour and delivery which put a lot of extra stress on his heart rate which had dropped multiple times keeping everyone on their toes.

Our incredible team of nurses and doctors, along with us had come to the decision to delivery via C Section at 6:57pm after another scary drop in vitals. 

While the doctor was on the phone with the operating room to rush us there, my INCREDIBLY strong and determined wife decided that wasn’t how this delivery was going to end.

6 minutes later at 7:03PM Atlas blessed us with is entrance naturally and everyone in the room… nurses, doctors, even my wife were all in a state of shock and awe at the same time a huge wave of relief! 

There is so much more to his story and one day we will share that with you but for now we’re just embracing the world as a family of 4 with our little miracle boy 💙

the last year of my twenties 🤘🏻 begins today! 

Well well well, today I start my victory lap of my twenties! I’m not really much of a runner (clearly) so it will be a slow lap but a good one none the less 💪🏻

You know, I’ve thought a lot about what your 20’s are supposed to be all about and there are days where I think I did it wrong…but then I sit, on my couch in the home we’ve created fighting the urge to go and pick up my beautiful sleeping children and bring them into bed because I want to snuggle them and I think to myself… I am exactly where I am supposed to be 🤍

I have an incredible business, a huge support system, an army of cheerleaders and the most beautiful family, I look back on what I’ve accomplished so far in my 20’s and I’m fucking PROUD! 

A very often response I get from people throughout doing my job and from others in the business is “wow you’re only twenty(something)” I used to just laugh it off but as I near 30 I really start to understand how much I truly have accomplished and succeeded in! 

I also just want to mention that the closer I get to 30, the more humble I become 😂 (ya fuckin right)

The victory lap of my 20’s begins and I know that the next year is going to be amazing, challenging, exciting and full of new adventures! 

I’m expanding my career by going back to school to get my degree all while continuing the success of my business, raising a family and honestly just LIVING! 

So cheers to me (eww, I’m sorry for how douchey that sounds) ✨ May this next 365 days go really fucking slow and be filled with wild fucking memories! 🙌🏻

#communityovercompetition 

Here’s your Monday motivation… It’s something I’ve said countless times and it’s something I preach as often as I can!

Stop looking at other photographers as competition or comparing yourself to someone else. If you’re trying to be like someone else than you’re losing track of who you are! 

We should all be here to build each other up and fucking root the shit out of everyone’s accomplishments! There is room for all of us, there is room for everyone to succeed, the ceiling is as high as you want it too be! 

Follower counts don’t mean shit, the amount of bookings don’t make you successful, overworking isn’t a sign of being successful. Success is the ability to live your life and run your business how you want, as big or as little as you want and to create whatever you want!

This time of year for a lot of photographers equals burnout, self doubt, comparisons and questioning your skills… I’m here to tell you to put that shit away!

Change your mindset and go do something f*#king amazing, even if that means taking a nap! DO IT! You got this 💪🏻

#sorrynotsorry but the worst thing to happen to a wedding reception is an “open mic” portion of speeches. Nothing kills the mood more than unprepared speeches one after the other. 

My BIGGEST piece of advice is to invite only a select number of people to give a speech (from those who really mean the most to you) and avoid the open mic that can and most likely will turn into awkward cringy moments being told, repetitive stories and some alcohol influenced words! 

I’m not sure when the norm of wedding toasts turned into wedding speeches. Toast the couple, say a few sweet words, even make a joke but keep it short and to the point! 🤘🏻
